translated: Carlander, Olof Andrew, landowner, Blombacka, Kålltorp, born on November 6, 1874 in Gothenburg to the wholesale merchant Christopher C. and Isabella Bourn. Married in 1906 to Louise von Hofsten. Children: Lennart born in 1907, Ingrid born in 1909, Margareta born in 1914, and Olof born in 1916. Studied agriculture in Scotland and Sweden from 1892 to 1897. Owns Blombacka since 1897. Board member in Västergötland. Member of the Gothenburg Guild. Director of Skara-Stenstorp and Mariestads-Moholm railway. Board member of the Göta Canal Company. Holder of The Royal Order of Vasa, The Order of the North Star and The badge of honor of Skaraborg's Agricultural Society.
